    "recap_headline": "University of Northern Colorado Athletics",
    "recap_text": "GREELEY, Colo.\n\u2013 Northern Colorado opened conference play Saturday afternoon with an 8\u20135 loss to St. Thomas at Jackson Field.\nThe Bears collected 12 hits in the contest and erased an early deficit, but a late offensive surge from the Tommies proved to be the difference.\nSt. Thomas struck first with a run in the opening inning before Northern Colorado answered in the second. An RBI triple from\nEthan Mooser\nhighlighted a two-run frame that gave the Bears their first lead of the afternoon. The Tommies tied the game in the fourth, but Northern Colorado again responded in the sixth when\nZeke Minic\nlaunched a home run and\nLogan Pruski\nfollowed with a solo shot to even the score at 4\u20134.\nSt. Thomas regained control late, scoring one run in the seventh before adding three more in the ninth to extend its lead. Northern Colorado plated one run in the bottom of the ninth but could not complete the comeback.\nPruski led the Bears offensively with three hits and an RBI, while Minic added two hits and a home run. Mooser and\nEthan Fillinger\neach recorded multi-hit efforts as the Bears finished with 12 hits.\nGame 1 \u2013 St. Thomas 8, Northern Colorado 5\nUNC bounced back in the second game of Saturday's doubleheader, defeating St. Thomas 9\u20134 to earn its first conference victory of the season at Jackson Field. The Bears offense came alive with 15 hits, scoring in four different innings to secure the win.\nSt. Thomas jumped out to an early lead with two runs in the first and two more in the third, but Northern Colorado steadily chipped away. The Bears plated single runs in the first and second innings before taking the lead with a two-run third.\nZeke Minic\nprovided a spark with a two-run home run, while\nMason Griffin\nlater added a solo shot. UNC created separation late in the game, scoring two runs in the seventh and three more in the eighth to seal the victory.\nBrett Barber\ndrove in three runs and scored twice to lead the Bears, while\nJake Bullard\nadded two RBIs. Mooser and\nLogan Pruski\neach contributed two hits as part of the 15-hit effort.\nOn the mound,\nJake Storey\nstruck out eight over 6.2 innings before\nLucas Stone\nearned the win in relief and\nBrady Hudson\nclosed out the game.\nGame 2 \u00a0\u2013 Northern Colorado 9, St. Thomas 4\nON DECK:\nNorthern Colorado heads on the road, beginning with a two-game midweek series at No. 6 Arkansas in Fayetteville. The Bears will then travel to Omaha, Nebraska, to resume Summit League play with a three-game series against the Mavericks starting Friday, March 20.\nDIAMOND CLUB\nThe Diamond Club plays a vital role in supporting the UNC Baseball program. By giving to the Diamond Club, you help provide access to facility enhancements\u2014such as the Jackson Field Turf Project\u2014along with advanced technology and elevated daily operations, giving our student-athletes the resources to compete and excel at the highest level.\nGive to the Diamond Club today!\nFOLLOW THE BEARS\nFor complete coverage of UNC Athletics, visit uncbears.com. Follow the baseball team on X (formerly Twitter) (@UNC_BearsBSB) and Instagram (@UNC_BearsBaseball)."
